  "prompt": "Is there a way to see someones likes on instagram?",
  "response": "As of my knowledge cutoff in October 2023, Instagram does not offer a direct feature that allows users to see all the posts someone else has liked. However, you can potentially see some interactions by checking mutual friends' posts or public posts if the person has commented or liked them. \n\nHere are a few ways you might get an idea of someone's likes:\n\n1. **Mutual Friends**: If you have mutual friends with the person, you might see their likes on posts from mutual friends.\n2. **Activity Status**: Previously, Instagram had a \"Following\" tab in the Activity feed where you could see the activity of people you follow, including likes and comments. This feature was removed in 2019.\n3. **Public Posts**: If the person has liked or commented on public posts, you will be able to see this if you visit the post itself.\n\nInstagram prioritizes privacy, so accessing detailed information about someone's likes is restricted to protect user data and interactions. Always respect privacy and boundaries in social media interactions.\n\nFor the latest updates or changes in Instagram features, checking Instagram\u2019s official website or help center is recommended.",
